1
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:26,200
Thieves only have one rule. Kill first.

2
00:02:26,280 --> 00:02:27,880
If you dare to swing
that axe at me, just do it.

3
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:30,560
It's my love and my memory.

4
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,640
<i>Do what I say,</i>

5
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:35,560
<i>and you'll get everything</i>
<i>that belonged to that old man Paisal.</i>

6
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:39,320
- I don't see how it's fast.
- Listen carefully.

7
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:40,960
Ugh…

8
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,720
And why don't you use Pin
to tempt Yai instead of me?

9
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:46,800
It's obvious that she's leading Yai on.

10
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,360
- Pinanong.
- Madam?

11
00:03:03,880 --> 00:03:05,440
Why did you go see Yai at the resort?

12
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:08,840
Oh, I went to help Ms. Nee.

13
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,480
She was stuck inside the bathroom.

14
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:14,400
You went there purposefully
to stop her and Yai, huh?

15
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,600
The housekeeper heard the screaming
and took me there.

16
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,160
You said I stopped them.

17
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,760
What exactly did I stop them from doing?

18
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,960
What were Mr. Yai and Ms. Nee going to do?

19
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,680
Don't do anything behind my back.

20
00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:33,520
Your mother survived

21
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:36,320
because of the money I transferred.

22
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:38,920
Never forget that you owe me.

23
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,360
That money…

24
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:44,920
What's happening?

25
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,560
- Oh.
- Mom.

26
00:03:47,640 --> 00:03:50,000
Oh, it's nothing.

27
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:53,840
I just came to see if there was
anything missing for you during recovery,

28
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:56,000
so I could have Noi arrange it for you.

29
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,880
Pin, bow and thank Madam.

30
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:10,360
One day, when I'm no longer here,

31
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:12,560
you must take care of her for me.

32
00:04:12,640 --> 00:04:14,000
Do you understand?

33
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,400
Pin.

34
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,600
Take care of yourself.

35
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:39,520
Yes.

36
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:14,400
Pin.

37
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:18,320
I'm worried about Madam.

38
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:22,080
I'm worried about Mr. Na and Ms. Nee.

39
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,960
Now that Mr. Yai is back,

40
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:27,920
Paisal Farm
will definitely not be peaceful.

41
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:32,280
Don't worry too much, Mom.

42
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:36,640
Mr. Yai isn't that bad.

43
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:41,480
Hey, don't you lie to me.

44
00:05:42,400 --> 00:05:44,480
Madam told me everything

45
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,960
about how Mr. Yai caused chaos here.

46
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:50,680
I heard he went on a robbery spree
after disappearing.

47
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,200
You must be very careful.

48
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:58,160
Don't go anywhere near a vile person
like that. It's dangerous.

49
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:04,400
Yes, Mom.

50
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:12,280
Mom. It's time to sleep.

51
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,000
<i>Is that clear? And your madam</i>

52
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:29,280
should consider
making a career out of lying.

53
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:34,000
Where did you get all that money, Mr. Yai?

54
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,800
Where else would
a thief like me get it from

55
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:42,000
but gambling dens,
brothels, and smuggling?

56
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:47,800
I'll try to pay you back
as soon as possible.

57
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:51,320
But please don't tell Mom, okay?

58
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,400
I'll have to see how you behave first.

59
00:06:56,480 --> 00:07:00,040
If you make me happy,
it will remain a secret

60
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,160
forever.

61
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,600
MR. TATSANA

62
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,360
Hello, Mr. Na.

63
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,360
What's the problem at the farm, Pin?

64
00:07:27,440 --> 00:07:30,000
Why would Auntie want me
to put off my return trip?

65
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,120
I don't have any money now.

66
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,600
How can I stay here?

67
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,040
Did someone rob you?

68
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:41,680
Well, I didn't want to tell Auntie.

69
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,840
She'd be concerned.

70
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:45,600
Uh, Pin.

71
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,160
Do you have any money I can borrow?

72
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,960
20,000 would do.

73
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,360
I'll ask Auntie to return it
as soon as possible.

74
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,040
Well…

75
00:07:55,840 --> 00:07:57,960
I'd really like to help you,

76
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,120
but my mom just had surgery.

77
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:02,000
I spent all the money.

78
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:06,320
Pin? Pin? Hello, Pin.

79
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,520
Mr. Na?

80
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:09,880
Can you hear me, Mr. Na?

81
00:08:11,120 --> 00:08:13,880
I can't hear you, Pin.
You're breaking up. Hello, Pin.

82
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,920
Pin.

83
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:19,400
Who's that Pin?

84
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:26,160
Well, she's a maid back at my home.

85
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,800
Can we go shopping now?

86
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:35,120
We still have quite a few more gifts
to get for our families in Thailand.

87
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:36,799
Well…

88
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,080
my aunt transferred the money,

89
00:08:39,159 --> 00:08:41,000
but she accidentally sent it
to the wrong account.

90
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,760
I don't know whose account it went to.

91
00:08:42,840 --> 00:08:44,000
We're looking into it.

92
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,400
It's giving me a headache.

93
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:51,960
Please don't worry too much.

94
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:54,280
You can use my money first.

95
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:57,000
What's mine is yours anyway.

96
00:08:57,520 --> 00:09:01,560
When we get married,
we'll only need one wallet, right?

97
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:04,240
Don't worry, okay?

98
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:11,160
You're so nice to me.

99
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,080
How could I ever leave you?

100
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,600
- Pan Pan. Wait.
- Yai.

101
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,760
You jerk.

102
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:23,600
You told people my dad is a bandit.

103
00:09:23,680 --> 00:09:25,200
That's your fault.

104
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:26,720
You showed up without telling me.

105
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:31,120
Oh? You disappeared,
so I had to disguise myself and sneak in.

106
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:35,520
You call this a disguise? Ugh, Pan.

107
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,080
You stand out like a sore thumb.

108
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:39,560
People would notice you
from the next planet.

109
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,720
This is what
people wear on a farm, isn't it?

110
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,480
Stop complaining.

111
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:48,200
So what did you get by coming here so far?

112
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,680
- Nothing yet.
- Huh?

113
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:55,320
Does that mean
you're just here to mess around?

114
00:09:55,400 --> 00:09:56,880
It's not like that.

115
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:59,200
I just wanted to get
my stepmother to lower her guard

116
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:01,200
and reveal her dark secrets.

117
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,760
But that's risky.

118
00:10:03,640 --> 00:10:04,920
Then you should help me.

119
00:10:06,720 --> 00:10:07,680
No way.

120
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:09,640
Every worker here talks with their fists.

121
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:11,000
Hey, hey. Wait, Pan.

122
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,720
Who would dare do anything to you?

123
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,720
Hey, remember.

124
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:17,120
You're now Pan of Pa Wai,

125
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,000
the outlaw of the borderlands.

126
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,680
Ugh.

127
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:22,880
No, I'm not doing that.

128
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,560
Okay. Then go.

129
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,520
This time,
if you get beaten up, I won't help.

130
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:30,240
Yai, you jerk.

131
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:34,120
- Come here.
- Ow.

132
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,040
Being with me requires patience.

133
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,800
I'll teach you
how to defend yourself, Pan.

134
00:10:38,880 --> 00:10:40,640
Ugh! Ew.

135
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,840
That's creepy.

136
00:10:42,440 --> 00:10:43,680
Sleep here tonight.

137
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,720
I'll introduce you to everyone tomorrow.

138
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,800
Ugh.

139
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:53,280
Not this again.

140
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,640
He's forcing me again.

141
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,000
Hey.

142
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:02,440
Wait for that bastard.

143
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:06,200
When he gets here,
go bow and apologize to him.

144
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,880
What? At that time,

145
00:11:09,960 --> 00:11:12,800
I already bowed at his chest.

146
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:14,800
Do I need to bow even lower?

147
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,680
Hey, I'll ask him

148
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,600
to take you on as his assistant for now.

149
00:11:21,680 --> 00:11:23,520
And when the time is right,

150
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,320
make him your husband.

151
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:29,960
Use every trick you have in your arsenal.

152
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:37,360
Well, why don't you try
getting with that weirdo yourself?

153
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:40,400
In case you get bored of bland types

154
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,120
like Manager Teera.

155
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:43,560
- Ugh, Nee…
- Oh.

156
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,920
Good timing. You're both here.

157
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:51,640
Mr. Yai wouldn't hold a grudge
against my dear niece.

158
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,240
Mr. Yai.

159
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:57,920
Nee would like
to sincerely apologize to you

160
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,600
for cursing you that day.

161
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:02,720
- Noi.
- Yes, Madam?

162
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,320
Bring out the tray.

163
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:07,360
- The tray?
- The tray we've prepared.

164
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:08,840
Oh, yes.

165
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:20,840
I apologize for my disrespectful
behavior towards you, Mr. Yai.

166
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:39,680
- I forgive you. We're like siblings.
- Auntie…

167
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:41,600
Don't worry about it, alright?

168
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:45,640
I'm glad to see siblings getting along.

169
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:49,640
I have one more favor
to ask of you, Mr. Yai.

170
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,080
- So…
- Hey!

171
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,160
Bandit Yai.

172
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,080
Auntie.

173
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,760
It's him.

174
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:07,400
The… The thief
who was trying to steal a truck.

175
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,960
Report him to the police, Auntie.

176
00:13:12,160 --> 00:13:14,360
Calm down, Nee.

177
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,560
Come.

178
00:13:17,160 --> 00:13:18,640
Don't you remember your old friend?

179
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,680
This is Bandit Pan.

180
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,360
Bandit Pan?

181
00:13:29,560 --> 00:13:32,200
Don't tell me you're…

182
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:35,000
Pan of Pa Wai,

183
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:37,400
the outlaw of the borderlands.

184
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:42,600
Pan, son of…

185
00:13:43,600 --> 00:13:46,000
that worker Pload who was fired?

186
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,480
That's right, Auntie.

187
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:51,800
After being dismissed from the farm,

188
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:54,720
Uncle Pload headed south
and founded a band of thieves

189
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,880
that robbed and slaughtered people.

190
00:13:57,920 --> 00:13:59,720
After I fled and joined his band,

191
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,840
Pan and I fought shoulder to shoulder
along the border.

192
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:04,840
This one is a real cutthroat.

193
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,360
I don't want to brag.

194
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,560
A single shot, followed by total silence.

195
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:13,440
Stop it.

196
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:19,960
Are you two real men or not?

197
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,200
Why are you bullying women?

198
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:25,680
Hey, hey.
Be more careful with the gun, Pan.

199
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,680
It doesn't choose its target.
It could go bang!

200
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:31,160
Someone could have a hole
in their head just like your last victim.

201
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,120
It was a joke.

202
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:37,120
Let's not stress the ladies out.

203
00:14:38,560 --> 00:14:39,480
Madam.

204
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:43,160
I left it all behind,
and my hands are clean now

205
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:44,960
I'm tired of the smell of blood.

206
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:48,480
Okay, okay. Enough of the introduction.

207
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:50,920
From now on,

208
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:54,040
Bandit Pan will assist me
in running this farm.

209
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,160
Are you okay with that, Auntie?

210
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:00,520
No problem at all.

211
00:15:01,120 --> 00:15:02,600
I'm glad you have someone so skilled

212
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:03,800
to help you.

213
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:08,240
Okay! Let's go, Bandit.

214
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:12,240
Let's break out
the "green tea" tonight and celebrate.

215
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,880
Hey, wait.

216
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,240
Put the gun away, will you?

217
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:18,960
Or the ladies will be afraid of you.

218
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:20,680
- Let's go.
- Come on.

219
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:32,800
Is this place becoming a den of thieves?

220
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:39,960
Madam, did you see how vile they are?

221
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:42,480
It's dangerous to have them in the house.

222
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,720
What can I do?

223
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:49,040
You already saw how terrifying they are.

224
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:52,880
I'm at a disadvantage in every way.

225
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:54,760
What can I do?

226
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:11,840
Hello.

227
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:13,840
Hello, everyone.

228
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:17,560
Smith, wanna come greet your fans?

229
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,440
We're live again,

230
00:16:22,520 --> 00:16:24,960
but today is more special than usual

231
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:27,480
because we have
something good for you all.

232
00:16:27,560 --> 00:16:28,840
And those are…

233
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:31,320
Ta-da!

234
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,120
Here they are.

235
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:36,200
Wow, so cute.

236
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:38,880
Do you think it's cute?

237
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:42,160
For those who miss Smith,

238
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:44,280
Angel, or Aura,

239
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:47,240
you can now hug them at home
in the form of plushies.

240
00:16:47,320 --> 00:16:48,240
Available in four sizes.

241
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:51,400
XL, L, M, and S.

242
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:55,480
You can even get a whole family
of these cuties for yourself. Here.

243
00:16:56,360 --> 00:16:59,680
So cute. Isn't it cute?

244
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:15,680
Hiya, little doggie. Are you hungry?

245
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:17,119
You hungry?

246
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:25,040
Your cartilage
must be nice and crunchy, huh?

247
00:17:25,119 --> 00:17:27,359
‪You're getting fat. Should I eat you?

248
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:29,560
Who told you to wander around out here?

249
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:32,320
Pin will scold you. Get out of here.

250
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:33,800
Wait.

251
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,360
Where is Pin?

252
00:17:42,480 --> 00:17:44,640
Thank you, everyone.

253
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:47,640
See you next time for another live stream.

254
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,080
Bye-bye.

255
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:51,240
Smith, come say bye-bye.

256
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:54,520
Bye-bye. Thank you so much.

257
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,240
‪-Yay!
‪-Yeah!

258
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:02,000
- Woo!
- All 100 of them sold,

259
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,160
not a single one left.

260
00:18:03,240 --> 00:18:04,840
I messed up my hands cutting the fabric.

261
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:07,440
I'd be heartbroken if they didn't sell.

262
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:11,240
Thank you all so much
for helping sew the plushies.

263
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:13,600
If we work together like this,

264
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:16,840
even though our salaries are delayed,
we will survive.

265
00:18:17,440 --> 00:18:19,560
Great. We'll help pack and ship them,

266
00:18:19,640 --> 00:18:20,960
so they arrive to the customers quickly.

267
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:21,920
Guys, let's go.

268
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:24,400
- I'll leave it to you.
- Right.

269
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,400
Come on.

270
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:33,880
They sewed these plushies overnight.

271
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:35,800
Is it gonna be worth it?

272
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:41,120
After deducting the cost
and paying the workers who helped,

273
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,320
there will be some money left for Mr. Na.

274
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,760
Even if it's not much,

275
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:48,640
I'm still willing to help him out.

276
00:18:52,080 --> 00:18:55,120
Oh, Ms. Jin, what are you doing here?

277
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,960
No animal checkups today, right?

278
00:18:58,080 --> 00:19:01,440
Jin, don't tell Jom
I plan to give the money to Mr. Na.

279
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:05,960
I just missed my friend.

280
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,720
I wanted to see my friend.

281
00:19:07,800 --> 00:19:08,720
Can't I come by?

282
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:11,200
You wanted to see me?

283
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:14,640
You're still annoying as usual.

284
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:16,200
Wanna feel my fist?

285
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,000
Oh, let's not do that.

286
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:20,560
You'll end up crying
like you did in school.

287
00:19:21,640 --> 00:19:23,120
I recently started boxing classes.

288
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,000
Do you want to be the first to try me?

289
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:26,720
- Come here.
- What? Whoa.

290
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,520
- Jin. Jin.
- Move, Pin.

291
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:30,120
- I'll get you.
- Wait.

292
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:31,120
- Calm down.
- Help, Pin.

293
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,280
- Jom.
- Bleh!

294
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:33,640
- Stop it.
- Uh.

295
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:35,640
Whoa, Pin. Pin.

296
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:52,720
What's wrong, Pin?

297
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:56,760
I…

298
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,000
I'm okay.

299
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:04,680
I was sewing plushies all night,
so I probably

300
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:06,280
didn't get much sleep.

301
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:10,640
Pinanong.

302
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:17,320
Go cook something for me.

303
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:21,160
But Mom already made breakfast for you.

304
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:23,800
Your mom likes to make Western food.

305
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:26,200
It's too dry. I can't even swallow it.

306
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:31,240
Isn't that too much, Mr. Yai?

307
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,480
I know you're the boss.

308
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:34,920
But please be considerate of others, okay?

309
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,800
You always order Pin around.

310
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,320
And she's not even feeling well now.

311
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:45,640
Good. Then I'll order you instead.

312
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:47,640
Go slaughter a sheep for me.

313
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:49,960
I want it grilled.
Perfect match for sticky rice and chicken.

314
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:51,920
Go ahead.

315
00:20:53,360 --> 00:20:54,800
Our farm raises animals

316
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:57,680
for children to see,
not to be killed for food.

317
00:20:57,760 --> 00:21:00,320
Ugh, you just love to annoy me, don't you?

318
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:03,360
If you can't do it, I'll do it myself.

319
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:07,240
Hey. You think being a boss
makes you untouchable?

320
00:21:10,920 --> 00:21:12,880
Jom. Calm down.

321
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:15,600
Mr. Yai won't do it for real.

322
00:21:15,680 --> 00:21:19,320
What he said about selling dog meat
was just to scare us.

323
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:23,800
If you're challenging me like this,

324
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:27,880
perhaps I should show you
how much of a cutthroat I am.

325
00:21:35,160 --> 00:21:37,160
Let's start with this alpaca.

326
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:39,120
You'll soon find out I'm the real deal

327
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,520
and not a joke.

328
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,560
Mr. Yai!

329
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:53,000
Mr. Yai. That's enough, Mr. Yai.

330
00:21:55,480 --> 00:21:57,880
I'll go cook you a new meal.

331
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,840
Make it quick.

332
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:02,160
I'm getting hangry.

333
00:22:19,040 --> 00:22:20,200
That's Mr. Yai?

334
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,320
He's that bad, huh?

335
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:27,280
Someone like him will definitely
bring disaster to the farm.

336
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,760
Just wait and see.

337
00:22:37,920 --> 00:22:40,480
Stop flirting with the workers out there.

338
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:42,600
Just stay in the house.

339
00:22:43,240 --> 00:22:47,160
I was selling things on the live stream
to earn extra income for the workers.

340
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:50,040
I wasn't doing anything naughty,
as you might think.

341
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:56,040
Understood.

342
00:22:58,600 --> 00:23:01,960
So, what would you like to eat?

343
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:13,640
Um…

344
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,680
Chinese sausage rice. Can you make it?

345
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,800
I can make it.

346
00:23:22,360 --> 00:23:24,480
But I need a rice cooker.

347
00:23:25,920 --> 00:23:28,080
Would you like to wait at the table?

348
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:29,440
I'll bring it to you.

349
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,360
And why do you want Chinese sausage--

350
00:23:33,440 --> 00:23:35,640
Your job is to make it, so just make it.

351
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:37,720
I'll be watching here.

352
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:40,320
If you were to sneak
arsenic in there, I'd die.

353
00:23:42,720 --> 00:23:43,680
Go.

354
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:18,520
Don't forget to add ginkgo nuts.

355
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:25,640
I've brought you something different.

356
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:28,840
It's Chinese sausage rice.

357
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:32,240
I added ginkgo nuts,
exactly the way you liked.

358
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:37,040
Mom just taught me how to make it.

359
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:40,560
Please try it, Uncle.

360
00:26:52,560 --> 00:26:56,240
I'll stay here with you
until the incense burns out.

361
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,000
Uncle.

362
00:27:10,760 --> 00:27:12,240
I'm so sorry.

363
00:27:13,080 --> 00:27:15,120
If I've offended you,

364
00:27:16,280 --> 00:27:19,360
or if you're still worried about anything,

365
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:22,120
please appear in my dream.

366
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:27,520
Still the same puny crybaby.

367
00:27:56,120 --> 00:27:56,920
Hey!

368
00:27:58,080 --> 00:27:59,360
What are you doing here?

369
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:05,240
Are you an addict?

370
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:10,240
Or are you a thief
running from the police?!

371
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:14,040
I… I'm not any of that.

372
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:16,280
I'm homeless.

373
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:17,960
I have nowhere to go,
so I sleep around here.

374
00:28:18,040 --> 00:28:19,440
Please let me go.

375
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:20,600
Let him go.

376
00:28:20,680 --> 00:28:22,120
Please don't do anything to him.

377
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:27,280
Uh, wait.

378
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:31,400
Here. Take this to eat.

379
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:35,800
Whenever you're hungry,
you can ask me for food.

380
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:37,360
I'll keep some for you.

381
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:39,320
Don't go out and steal from anyone.

382
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:41,720
Take it.

383
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:44,520
Here.

384
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,920
Come eat with me.

385
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:57,600
There's still some left in the pot, right?

386
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:58,480
Come on.

387
00:30:01,080 --> 00:30:03,640
Um, I'm not hungry.

388
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:06,680
Please enjoy it. I need to get to work.

389
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:07,840
Sit down now.

390
00:30:30,600 --> 00:30:34,280
You have to eat it first,
so I can be sure it's safe.

391
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,360
What? Just a tiny bite?
Afraid of gaining weight or something?

392
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:59,240
Or are you so happy that you can't eat
after seeing my handsome face?

393
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:02,840
I'm not hungry.

394
00:31:02,920 --> 00:31:04,800
You have to eat it anyway, because I…

395
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:09,400
I'll make you eat
the veggies and sausages too.

396
00:31:10,720 --> 00:31:11,680
Here.

397
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:14,720
Thank you.

398
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,840
I'll get you some water.

399
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:16,840
Pin, what's wrong? Pin. Are you okay?

400
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:18,520
- Pin?
- I…

401
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:21,040
I'm okay. I'm just feeling dizzy.

402
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:26,360
Damn it, Yai. There you are. I'm starving…

403
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,680
Pan.

404
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:28,840
Go get the car key from Win.

405
00:32:28,920 --> 00:32:31,000
I'll take Pin to the hospital. Now!

406
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:32,680
Pin.

407
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:36,280
- Hurry up. Go now.
- Yeah.

408
00:32:46,240 --> 00:32:49,800
Here, Madam. Stir-fried cabbage
with shrimp, your favorite.

409
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:58,760
Noi, why aren't you serving the rice?

410
00:32:58,840 --> 00:32:59,920
What are you waiting for?

411
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:03,040
Madam told me not to.

412
00:33:03,120 --> 00:33:04,560
She wants to wait for Mr. Yai.

413
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:07,640
He's the owner of this house.

414
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:10,240
We should wait for him no matter what.

415
00:33:11,640 --> 00:33:13,960
Nee, go get that…

416
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:17,040
Go get Mr. Yai to eat with us.

417
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:18,720
I don't want to.

418
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:20,920
Don't make me repeat myself.

419
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:27,120
Madam, I'll go invite him myself.

420
00:33:31,080 --> 00:33:33,080
Mr. Yai's taking Pin to the hospital.

421
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:35,720
He said you all can eat without him.

422
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:37,920
Wow.

423
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:40,480
Everything looks delicious.

424
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,280
What happened to Pin?

425
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:50,760
Why is Mr. Tai taking her himself?

426
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,440
I don't know about that.

427
00:33:56,360 --> 00:33:59,840
If anyone wants to know,
ask Mr. Yai yourself.

428
00:34:08,719 --> 00:34:11,320
Hey. Jerd and Kan told me

429
00:34:11,400 --> 00:34:13,360
Yai brought another one
of his thief friends here.

430
00:34:13,440 --> 00:34:14,960
Is that true?

431
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:25,360
Watch your tone when you speak about him.

432
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:30,280
Who the hell are you?

433
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:33,360
Looking for trouble?

434
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:35,120
How many scars do you want?

435
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:39,400
Uh…

436
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:45,960
Stop it.

437
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:50,159
Calm down, both of you.

438
00:34:51,520 --> 00:34:55,120
Teera. You haven't met Mr. Pan,

439
00:34:55,199 --> 00:34:58,440
the son of one
of the former employees here, right?

440
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:04,240
And he's now Bandit Pload of Padang Besar.

441
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:07,480
And I'm Pan of Pa Wai,

442
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:09,160
the right-hand man of Mr. Yai, Chalit.

443
00:35:12,200 --> 00:35:15,120
Okay. Now that you know each other,

444
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:17,680
let's enjoy the meal. Please.

445
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:38,640
I'm not eating, Auntie.

446
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,080
I've lost my appetite.

447
00:35:40,720 --> 00:35:42,600
- Hey.
- Hey.

448
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:44,240
No need to be afraid.

449
00:35:44,320 --> 00:35:45,880
I've sanitized myself with alcohol spray.

450
00:35:45,960 --> 00:35:47,560
You won't get any thief germs from me.

451
00:35:51,480 --> 00:35:52,600
- Serve the rice!
- Yes.

452
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:54,520
Yes, yes. The rice.

453
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,560
This is Aunt Da.

454
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:16,720
She used to help care for Uncle Paisal.

455
00:36:17,520 --> 00:36:19,520
Auntie, this is…

456
00:36:20,120 --> 00:36:21,480
I'm a worker at the farm.

457
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:23,400
I brought Ms. Pin for a checkup.

458
00:36:26,720 --> 00:36:28,960
I couldn't ask you
while the doctor was there.

459
00:36:29,040 --> 00:36:31,400
There were rumors that
Mr. Yai, Mr. Paisal's son,

460
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:33,200
has returned to the farm. Is that true?

461
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:35,280
Poor father.

462
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:37,760
Before Mr. Paisal passed away,

463
00:36:37,840 --> 00:36:40,800
he kept calling out Mr. Yai's name.

464
00:36:40,880 --> 00:36:42,760
He must have missed his son dearly.

465
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:46,600
But his son never visited him even once.

466
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:53,800
I need to get back to work.

467
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:56,080
Send my regards to your mother.

468
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:59,160
Yes. Goodbye.

469
00:37:05,560 --> 00:37:08,960
Why didn't you tell her
that you're Mr. Paisal's son?

470
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,080
Look at me.

471
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:13,000
Who would believe me if I said it?

472
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:16,080
Oh, what did the doctor say?

473
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:19,080
I'm just a bit sleep-deprived,

474
00:37:19,160 --> 00:37:20,840
but the doctor gave me an injection.

475
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:23,760
I can go home
after receiving the medicine.

476
00:37:30,560 --> 00:37:33,040
Well, I'm afraid you'll fall
and hit your head,

477
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:35,040
and we'd have to pay extra.

478
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:06,280
Thank you.

479
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:39,160
Where is she?

480
00:38:48,640 --> 00:38:49,600
Hey.

481
00:38:50,880 --> 00:38:53,600
Pin. Why didn't you pick up when I called?

482
00:38:55,400 --> 00:38:57,320
- I…
- Ugh.

483
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:58,760
Come with me right now.

484
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:00,720
Mom.

485
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:05,320
Madam.

486
00:39:05,400 --> 00:39:07,440
She didn't really want to go with Mr. Yai.

487
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:10,920
But she wasn't feeling well,
and Mr. Yai happened to come by.

488
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,720
No need to say anything. I understand.

489
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:19,400
She must have thought
I wasn't good enough to protect her,

490
00:39:19,480 --> 00:39:21,040
so she relied on Yai.

491
00:39:21,920 --> 00:39:23,280
I don't blame you, Un.

492
00:39:24,800 --> 00:39:26,760
No, Madam.

493
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:29,880
I guarantee you with my life,
Pin would never do that.

494
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,360
Yes, Madam.

495
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:35,720
Mr. Yai didn't give me much.

496
00:39:35,800 --> 00:39:38,000
He just paid
for the doctor's fees and the medicine.

497
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:42,280
He paid for the doctor and medicine now,

498
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:45,000
but next time,
he'll probably give you more.

499
00:39:46,440 --> 00:39:48,600
I thought a thief like him was bad,

500
00:39:49,160 --> 00:39:51,600
but you're even worse.

501
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:55,240
Your daughter is something else, Un.

502
00:39:56,160 --> 00:39:57,400
I give up.

503
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:02,400
But I never thought anything bad
like what you're saying.

504
00:40:05,320 --> 00:40:06,400
Pin.

505
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:09,360
How dare you talk to her like that?

506
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,720
Apologize to her right now.

507
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:12,360
But I didn't…

508
00:40:12,440 --> 00:40:13,480
Forget it.

509
00:40:14,440 --> 00:40:15,440
Right now,

510
00:40:15,520 --> 00:40:17,400
I'm all by myself,

511
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:20,880
just waiting for the day
I'll get banished from this farm.

512
00:40:25,680 --> 00:40:27,200
I just never imagined

513
00:40:28,360 --> 00:40:30,600
that the person I loved and trusted most…

514
00:40:33,640 --> 00:40:34,960
would betray me.

515
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:50,520
Mom.

516
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:05,800
Sit on the floor.

517
00:41:09,440 --> 00:41:10,680
Why, Mom?

518
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:12,600
I said sit on the floor.

519
00:41:21,600 --> 00:41:23,000
Put your hands together
and prepare to swear.

520
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:28,240
Swear? What am I swearing?

521
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:31,320
Just do what I say. Don't ask questions.

522
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:37,760
Say it.

523
00:41:38,960 --> 00:41:42,880
Swear to this statue
that you will never betray Madam

524
00:41:43,640 --> 00:41:47,000
by siding with
or helping Mr. Yai in harming her.

525
00:41:48,240 --> 00:41:50,000
But I never intended to do that.

526
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:51,600
But you broke my trust.

527
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:55,760
And it's the only way to make sure
you won't be fooled by Mr. Yai.

528
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:58,640
Say it.

529
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:08,560
If I do it,

530
00:42:09,520 --> 00:42:12,160
you'll feel better and stop stressing

531
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:14,520
or overthinking, right?

532
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:16,760
Yes.

533
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:24,640
I swear I will never betray Madam.

534
00:42:25,280 --> 00:42:27,200
If you break your oath,

535
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:30,120
may I die a painful death.

536
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:34,400
No. I won't say that.

537
00:42:35,680 --> 00:42:37,960
How could I ever
put your life at stake for an oath?

538
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:39,560
I told you to swear.

539
00:42:40,640 --> 00:42:41,880
Otherwise,

540
00:42:42,480 --> 00:42:43,560
all ties between us

541
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:46,000
will be severed from now on.

542
00:42:46,080 --> 00:42:48,160
When I die, don't even come to my funeral.

543
00:43:54,520 --> 00:43:55,520
Ooh.

544
00:44:04,840 --> 00:44:06,000
That is my mom's.

545
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:09,280
- Give it back.
- It will be mine anyway.

546
00:44:09,360 --> 00:44:11,040
- Give it.
- It's mine.

547
00:44:11,120 --> 00:44:12,560
- It's my mom's!
- Ah.

548
00:44:35,560 --> 00:44:39,160
Mr. Yai was trying
to steal something from the safe.

549
00:44:40,560 --> 00:44:43,640
I tried to tell him to go ask you first.

550
00:44:43,720 --> 00:44:45,800
But…

551
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:48,560
But then he hurt me…

552
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:53,280
Ow. It hurts.

553
00:45:11,920 --> 00:45:14,720
I didn't come back
because I wanted Dad's stupid inheritance.

554
00:45:14,800 --> 00:45:17,040
<i>I need some men to handle him.</i>

555
00:45:17,120 --> 00:45:20,640
<i>Ten percent of the inheritance will be</i>
<i>transferred to your account immediately.</i>

556
00:45:20,720 --> 00:45:22,080
And I'll also let you have someone.

557
00:45:22,160 --> 00:45:23,800
We meet again.

558
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:25,440
It's clearly fate.

559
00:45:25,520 --> 00:45:28,240
<i>May you and her be together</i>
<i>in the same grave</i>

560
00:45:28,320 --> 00:45:30,640
until the end of time, Mr. Chalit.

561
00:45:30,720 --> 00:45:32,120
I'll be waiting for you, Mr. Yai.

562
00:46:16,680 --> 00:46:18,960
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
